<TITLE> Portugal's Andrade to miss Euro 2008 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LISBON, March 14 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Portuguese defender Jorge Andrade had surgery on his left knee on Thursday and is likely to miss the European Championship finals, the Lusa news agency said, quoting a hospital source. It gave no indication of how long it would take the 29-year-old to recover but said the Juventus defender will be out of Euro 2008, co-hosted by Switzerland and Austria from June 7-29. The operation was performed by a Portuguese medical team headed by Antonio Martins and attended by the Serie A club's doctor. The centre-back joined Juventus from Deportivo Coruna this season. Andrade also missed the 2006 World Cup in Germany after knee surgery
